            <h4>
                Te Whariki (Early childhood curriculum)</h4>
            <p>
                These are the National ECE guidelines, which the crèche programme is based on. It
                encompasses 4 principles: Family and Community, Holistic Development, Empowerment,
                and Relationships, which concentrate on developing the child’s sense of belonging,
                well-being, contribution, communication and exploration of the environment. It is
                our guide for providing and achieving a quality programme appropriate for your child.
                Copies of Te Whariki are available at the crèche for parents to take home to read.</p>
